name: Toxic Rick
line: Relax, quit your bitching. Y-You’re gonna be fine. Grandpa’s here.

name: Rick
line: Hahahahahaha.

name: Toxic Rick
line: You think that’s funny?

name: Rick
line: Y-You got to have a sense of humor about these things. Oh, wait, you can’t. You’re literally incapable of seeing the bigger picture. I guess it’s just funny because you’ve never done anything but complain about me being in charge, but if I ever gave you the wheel we’d be dead in five minutes.

name: Toxic Morty
line: Ah, Rick?

name: Rick
line: You poor, dumb, sick animal.

name: Toxic Morty
line: Augh... Rick?

name: Toxic Rick
line: Ahh! (Gets up and walks towards Rick.) Just do it! Just do it, you piece of-

name: Rick
line: Aaahhh! I’m back, baby! (Dances around.) Regular Rick! Master of both worlds! Check it it out! (Farts in Morty's face.) Excuse me. (Walks up to the lever.) Now we’ll just reverse this hacky toxicity beam. Man, I really over think shit when I’m angry.

name: Priest
line: God is not a lie.

name: Crying boy
line: Mommy! Mommy!

name: Rick
line: (Looking around with binoculars.) Ha! All right, Morty, now it’s time we re-merge your little ass.

name: Morty
line: You’re a better man than me, Rick. I’m healthy enough to admit that!

name: Rick
line: That kid is a real piece of shit.

name: Toxic Morty
line: (Moaning in pain.) Y-Y-You’re gonna save me, right?

name: Rick
line: (Picks up Toxic Morty.) Part of me wanted to, Toxic Morty. Part of me really wanted to. (He sticks the injection into Toxic Morty.)

name: Worker
line: (On the phone.) I’m telling you, these shares are hot.

name: Morty
line: (Also on the phone.) Duane, Duane, Duane, I get it, now can you get me? Have I ever lied to you? (Grabs an apple on his desk.) That’s right, and ask around, I never do, Duane.

name: Morty
line: Let me put this real simple. This stock is a beautiful redhead, recently single, not looking to date but ready to fall in love, and fate has put her locker two down from yours, Duane Two lockers down. (Winks at two female workers. They both giggle.) So step up or step off, Duane. Blue pill or red pill, what’ll be, bro? Totally understand, Duane. You’re the boss. (Stops the call.) Heinholz Biotech Million and a half at thirty-three. (Bites the apple as everyone cheers and throws their papers.)

name: Worker in a red shirt
line: (Catches the apple.) Heh.You little fucking monster.

name: Morty
line: Mmm! Is this organic? Mmm! (Morty's phone rings, and he answers, as he walks up to his window at the view.) Go for Morty.

name: Jessica on the phone
line: Hi, Morty. It’s Jessica. Look, can we just talk for a minute?

name: Morty
line: Is that how long it takes for Rick to trace my location?

name: Jessica
line: Come back, Morty. I miss you.

name: Morty
line: You miss the old me. You miss someone that loved you so much you never had to love ‘em back.

name: Jessica
line: How do you know I don’t want to love you?

name: Morty
line: Because I’m not sick. (Presses a button.)

name: Jacquelyn
line: (Sits at the bench.) Ex-girlfriend? Should I be jealous?

name: Morty
line: (Puts his phone on the bench.) There’s nothing to be jealous of.

name: Jacquelyn
line: (Sigh) I just realized that I’m scheduled to speak at that fundraiser on our date night. I can cancel.

name: Morty
line: We’ll be together. That’s a date.

name: Jacquelyn
line: You are the perfect man. (Notices Morty's phone.) Oh, sweetie, (Picks it up to show Morty.) I think you hit the wrong button. You didn’t hang up.

name: Morty
line: Huh. How ‘bout that?

name: Rick
line: Sorry, tiny American Psycho, (Holds up the injection.) time to take the opposite of your medicine.

name: Morty
line: Do what you got to do.

name: Morty
line: Oh! Ow! Ahh! (Eventually, Morty gets up.)

name: Jessica
line: So, how do you feel, Morty?

name: Morty
line: Ah, geez. I’m miserable.

name: Rick
line: Am I good or what?

name: Morty
line: I guess it’s worth it, though, to know how much you care.

name: Jessica
line: Care? Me? Morty, I’m fine with you. I only did this for him. (Points at Rick.)

name: Rick
line: You lying bitch. She kept coming to our house, Morty, and kept asking me. "Did did d-did you get a new Morty yet?"

name: Jessica
line: Because you kept drunk dialing me and crying about it.

name: Rick
line: I wasn’t crying!

name: Morty
line: Jacquelyn, I I-I-I wasn’t who I said I was.

name: Jacquelyn
line: You weren’t a 14-year-old boy from the Midwest who ran away from his family and capitalized on his lack of conscience by becoming a stock broker?

name: Morty
line: Oh. I guess I was pretty up front about that, wasn’t I?

name: Jacquelyn
line: You were up front about everything. You were my soul mate.

name: Morty
line: Well No-Not anymore. I’ll, um Y-You can keep the apartment, and and and, uh the drones.

name: Rick
line: She can’t keep the drones. They turn into a little Voltron robot. They’re awesome.

name: Rick
line: You can’t keep the drones.

name: Girl 1
line: So, how was your date with Brad?

name: Jessica
line: It wasn’t a date. We were just having lunch.

name: Girl 2
line: You guys are getting back together, aren’t you?

name: Morty
line: (Looks down, sad.)

name: Rick
line: (Comes out of nowhere.) Morty, I need your help on an adventure. Eh, "need" is a strong word. We need door stops, but a brick would work, too.

name: Morty
line: Okay.

name: Jessica
line: Morty.

name: Morty
line: (Morty stops and looks at Jessica and smiles.)

name: Jessica
line: Good to have you back.

name: Girl 1
line: Have you ever been peed on before? Oh, my God. Yum.

name: Credits song
line: Hey, did you ever want to hold a terrifold? I got one right here Grab my terri-flap Squeeze it Grab it, squeeze it Tug on my terri-flap Hey, I want to take you to The terrifold dance Wanna come with me? You can grab my holdie-folds Squeeze ‘em tight You son of a bitch. Suck my holdie-flappy folds Lick my flappy foldie-holes My terri-flaps in your mouth Suck my flaps, you piece of shit. Whoo!

name: Man
line: Although only a handful of moon towers remain today, they were popular in the late 19th century. An entire town could be illuminated by... (He sees the containment unit.)  What the hell is this? (Out of curiosity, he presses a button, releasing toxin gas, and slimey Stacy. The man backs away, and accidentally falls off the tower, screaming all the way down.)

name: Stacey
line: Sea Cucumber! Sea Cucumber!!
